        {
          "key": "orientation_lecture_part1",
          "value": {
            "speakerName": "Professor Clark",
            "text": "Welcome, future stewards. This is your Final Practical Examination: The Stewardship Field Journal. You will spend a season in Riversong learning sustainable fishing. Your task is to catalog fish and practice deboning.",
            "showAsAction": true,
            "showConditions": [
              {
                "conditionType": 2,
                "conditionKey": "ORIENTATION_DAY_0",
                "conditionValue": "ACTIVE",
                "expectedBool": true
              }
            ],
            "triggersOnShow": [],
            "choices": [],
            "nextDialogId": "orientation_lecture_part2"
          }
        },
        {
          "key": "orientation_lecture_part2",
          "value": {
            "speakerName": "Professor Clark",
            "text": "You must also earn 2,000 gold to pay your outstanding tuition fees. Your work in Riversong serves as both your exam and your means to graduate. Your journal has two main objectives.",
            "showAsAction": true,
            "showConditions": [],
            "triggersOnShow": [],
            "choices": [],
            "nextDialogId": "orientation_lecture_part3"
          }
        },
        {
          "key": "orientation_lecture_part3",
          "value": {
            "speakerName": "Professor Clark",
            "text": "First: Wild Fishing Stewardship. Catch fish to catalog them in your journal. Practice sustainable fishing to keep the waters healthy. Second: Value Creation. Learn deboning to complete your journal entries and earn gold.",
            "showAsAction": true,
            "showConditions": [],
            "triggersOnShow": [],
            "choices": [],
            "nextDialogId": "orientation_lecture_part4"
          }
        },
        {
          "key": "orientation_lecture_part4",
          "value": {
            "speakerName": "Professor Clark",
            "text": "Your choices will define what kind of steward you become. Begin your journey to Riversong. Remember: This is about balance. Fish responsibly, process skillfully, and engage with the community.",
            "showAsAction": true,
            "showConditions": [],
            "triggersOnShow": [],
            "choices": [],
            "nextDialogId": "orientation_lecture_part5"
          }
        },
        {
          "key": "orientation_lecture_part5",
          "value": {
            "speakerName": "Professor Clark",
            "text": "Your journal will tell the story of your stewardship. The future of those waters depends on the choices you make. Achievement Unlocked: First Lesson.",
            "showAsAction": true,
            "showConditions": [],
            "triggersOnShow": [
              "CompleteQuest:ORIENTATION_DAY_0",
